content: Can we have the house election as well plz

Fun, but more customization, like why can't we change their names; and consistency (why does the ruling party just collapse ?) Imagine being able to name candidates and adjust there stats, also being able to edit the stats of the states to make them realistic.

I was running as an Independent in Massachusetts and I had in the last poll 87% to the Democrats 8% and the Republicans 5% and I then went on to loose to the Democrat by 5%. That's an 84% swing of bad polling! To put it in perspective, that's like DC flipping on the national level.
Glaring Problems including many bugs, no tutorial, and your party continually is at a low percent no matter what you do. Also party and staate representations are grossly wrong.

This game can be improved easily but it just seems lazy with no improvement over the UK edition. Regions have the wrong names, the president has no veto and no matter what, the governing party collapses in the next election with no strategy at all.

Still very little customization options, and for some reason they fail to capture what makes American politics unique. The executive powers. The president only use is to allow the senators more to create laws faster. The president themselves have no veto authority.
Good but need improvements! I think you need to improve the game such as the correct locations of different states, the incumbent, or gain/ loss of the seats, so many things need to be improved
The game's base mechanics works well, but incumbent Senators switch states and make ot hard to keep track. Parties need to be encouraged or forced to keep incumbents in one state.

Seems awfully random. Candidates with strong leads mysteriously lose elections, reputation seems to go negative easily but rarely goes positive and it's a ping pong of leading parties every election. In many cases, one party wins every state in the Presidential election -- which is about impossible.
